comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-06T16:47:47.400Z",codex-agent,Duplicate-check evidence used pm context pm search and open or in-progress lists. Net-new scope under pm-o7be for contract-driven completion option generation and append body parity.
  "2026-04-06T17:54:27.270Z",codex-agent,"Implemented contract-driven completion flag parity across bash/zsh/fish by sourcing append/completion flags from src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts via shared constants in completion generation. Added APPEND_FLAG_CONTRACTS and COMPLETION_FLAG_CONTRACTS, wired contracts --command <append|completion> --flags-only coverage, and updated help content to document eager/lazy behavior. Adjusted completion unit expectation to match generated shell choices after removing brittle quoted-shell-list assertion. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/pi-agent-extension.spec.ts tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/task-lifecycle-aliases.spec.ts (136/136 passed)."
  "2026-04-07T18:14:22.163Z",codex-agent,"2026-04-07 scope extension: completion candidate generation must derive from alias-aware command contracts so shell completion matches parser-accepted flags (underscore parity included)."
